<paragraph blockId="7.[151,826,513,575]" box="[151,295,548,575]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,287,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Figs 46–52</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,621,1152]" box="[151,1093,621,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">
Female. Measurements and external description as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Souza, S. P. &amp; Takiya, D. M. &amp; Felix, M." box="[753,1089,621,647]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" pagination="176 - 185" refId="ref8548" refString="Souza, S. P., Takiya, D. M. &amp; Felix, M. (2017) Two new Metacephalus DeLong &amp; Martinson, 1973 species (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Portanini) from Brazil and proposed synonymy with Paraportanus Carvalho &amp; Cavichioli, 2009. Zootaxa, 4281 (1), 176 - 185. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4281.1.16" type="journal article" year="2017">Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,621,1152]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">
Female terminalia. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[577,664,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subrectangular; posterior margin broadly convex medially; posterolateral angles rounded. “Internal” sternite VIII without sclerites. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1252,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately produced posteriorly, row of sparse macrosetae along ventroapical margin and few grouped on apical portion. Valvifer I, in lateral view, with dorsal and ventral margins convex; distal margin truncate. Valvula I (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Figs 48, 49</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, slightly broadened dorsally on apical portion, narrowing gradually towards acute apex; dorsal sculptured area extending from basal portion of blade to apex, formed mostly by rod-shaped elements; ventral sculptured area restricted to apical portion, formed by sparse scale-like processes. Valvula II (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1392,872,899]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Figs 50, 51</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately expanded beyond basal curvature, distinctly narrowed towards apex; without preapical prominence; apical portion triangular; apex narrowly rounded; dorsal margin with about 34 teeth; most teeth subtriangular or obtuse dorsally, short, with anterior and posterior portions oblique; denticles absent; ventral margin with long, subtriangular, not prominent teeth on apical portion, without denticles; blade surface with irregular granulate sculpturing, rod-shaped apically. Gonoplac (
<figureCitation box="[644,726,1052,1079]" captionStart="FIGURES 46–52" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" captionTargetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1437,1173,1775]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 46–52. Metacephalus sakakibarai Souza, Takiya &amp; Felix, 2017. Female: 46, sternite VII, ventral view; 47, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 48, valvifer I and valvula I, lateral view; 49, apical portion of valvula I; 50, valvifer II and valvula II, lateral view; 51, apical portion of valvula II; 52, gonoplac, lateral view. Scale bars: 46–52 = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, gradually expanded at median portion and then gradually narrowed posteriorly; apex obtuse; surface with numerous tiny denticuli apically and extending anteriorly along ventral margin, with few setae (about two or three) located apically.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3907638" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3907638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3907638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="576" startId="7.[151,264,1800,1825]" targetBox="[160,1434,1173,1768]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1800,1897]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1800,1825]" pageId="7" pageNumber="576">FIGURES 46–52.</emphasis>
